#Text=At what point was that for you ?
#Text=When I stopped drinking , of course .
#Text=But I could n’t play music in the way I wanted to play it anymore .
#Text=I would have been like a parody of myself .
#Text=So that did n’t seem truthful to me .
#Text=Trying to do comedy seemed truthful to me , but then , like I told you before , I did n’t have the discipline to do stand-up .
#Text=That term was n’t popular much before the seventies .
#Text=Then you started hearing these stand-up comics .
#Text=When I was a kid and when I was a teenager , doing comedy meant you were interrupting somebody ’s dinner in a restaurant .
#Text=There was no comedy clubs per se .
#Text=But the turning point — it ’s called survival .
#Text=It ’s like being a cockroach .
#Text=You evolve or die .
#Text=When I was kid I thought everybody was like me and all these people I hang with are going to be running the country and I could n’t have been more wrong .
#Text=West on politics
#Text=[ continued from previous section ]
#Text=Well they are .
#Text=It ’s just things have changed .
#Text=I ’m way older than a lot of these guys by the way , that are out there .
#Text=But to me they look like old men with bad breath and dandruff .
#Text=Who are you talking about ?
#Text=Republicans .
#Text=Yeah .
#Text=You know , the guys that are running things .
#Text=They do n’t look like people that came from my generation at all .
#Text=I ’m as old as Karl Rove , or any of those idiots and it ’s like , ' Where did you come from ? '

#Text=It ’s still the same old geezers that hide behind religion and family values , and then they ’re messing with guys in men ’s rooms and scandal prone because that ’s sort of what the party is famous for .
#Text=I hated those guys and I did n’t grow up to be one .
#Text=But then I watch all these people from my generation just suddenly morph into that and I ’m still in a state of shock .
#Text=Where did these Donna Reeds and these little Breck girls , St. Pauli girls that are filled with Republican ideology come from ?
#Text=It ’s like they ’re young .
#Text=What is this , you know .

#Text=It ’s confusing because you look at somebody like Dick Cheney , who has this lesbian daughter , who ’s in a gay marriage [ Poe and Cheney have not entered into a formal union - ed ] and now has a baby with her partner , and you just do n’t know how the situation exists .
#Text=It ’s hard to comprehend .
#Text=That Mary Cheney exists in the Republican party , and that she seems to be fine with that existence and even works for it .
